  "body": "I got wallet running on geth with my developer used fast syn, now this fast syn is crashing every 2-3 days.\r\n\r\nWhenever it crashes we use command\r\n\r\ngeth  --rpc --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --rpccorsdomain \"http://personaldomain.com\" --rpcapi \"db,net,ssh,eth,web3,personal\" --shh console --lightkdf --syncmode \"light\" --cache 1000\r\n\r\nSyn seems to start but eth.syncing = false , blocknumber shows correct, peers connected are 8\r\n\r\n> WARN [10-09|02:41:24] message loop                             peer=dc429a27a808e46d err=EOF\r\nINFO [10-09|02:41:32] Imported new block headers               count=1   elapsed=5.486ms   number=4349265 hash=1489e4…a14d78 ignored=0\r\nINFO [10-09|02:41:36] Imported new block headers               count=1   elapsed=10.361ms  number=4349266 hash=476c2b…8ace1f ignored=0\r\nWARN [10-09|02:42:01] message loop                             peer=dc429a27a808e46d err=EOF\r\nINFO [10-09|02:42:03] Imported new block headers               count=1   elapsed=5.218ms   number=4349267 hash=06b7ce…e07d28 ignored=0\r\nWARN [10-09|02:42:31] message loop                             peer=dc429a27a808e46d err=EOF\r\n> eth.syncing\r\nfalse\r\n> geth attachINFO [10-09|02:42:37] Imported new block headers               count=1   elapsed=6.910ms   number=4349268 hash=ea47ba…09a5a1 ignored=0\r\n> net.peerCount\r\n10\r\n> eth.blockNumber\r\n4349268\r\n> eth.syncing\r\nfalse\r\n> WARN [10-09|02:43:02] message loop                             peer=dc429a27a808e46d err=EOF\r\nINFO [10-09|02:43:05] Imported new block headers               count=1   elapsed=5.993ms   number=4349269 hash=c44332…f7d682 ignored=0\r\n\r\n\r\n but then  try to ControlA+D screen does not detach, it simply quits process i guess because when i again access screen it says no screen.\r\n\r\nAlso how can i switch to kinda of slow syn which as per my experience does not crash so frequently.",
